text: Malyye Gayny () is a rural locality (a village) in Kozhay-Semyonovsky Selsoviet, Miyakinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 62 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 27 km from Kirgiz-Miyaki, 6 km from Kozhay-Semyonovka. == References == Category:Rural localities in Miyakinsky District
title: Malyye Gayny
